The Risk Management Plan (RMP) was last updated on July 14, 2012.  This document provides a brief overview of the following elements of the RMP:



* The accidental release prevention and emergency response policies at the stationary source;

* The stationary source and regulated substances handled;

* The general accidental release prevention program and chemical-specific prevention steps;

* The five-year accident history;

* The emergency response program; and

* The planned changes to improve safety.



ACCIDENTAL RELEASE PREVENTION AND EMERGENCY RESPONSE POLICIES:



3M Elyria is committed to operating and maintaining all processes in a safe and responsible manner.  3M Elyria employees have had operating procedures training and perform ongoing preventative maintenance on process equipment.  3M Elyria uses a combination of accidental release prevention programs and emergency response planning programs to manage the hazards associated with the regulated chemicals used on site.  By maintaining these programs, 3M Elyria ensures the safety of plant personnel as well the safety of the public and the protection of the environment.     



STATIONARY SOURCE AND REGULATED SUBSTANCES:



3M Elyria produces cellulose sponges.  The process uses highly refined wood pulp as a raw material and carbon disulfide, the only toxic chemical regulated under 40 CFR 68 at 3M Elyria, is added to the batch reactor to facilitate the production of the cellulose sponges.  Carbon disulfide is stored on site in a railcar, two storage tanks, and/or multiple day tanks. 



